{"mem_mq0wm8pf_3d517ebbb016":{"concepts":["prose memory failure","self-token recovery block","syntax-gating","skip-the-reference","runtime enforcement vs stored warning","NCL parallel","OmniClaude continuity","anti-pattern migration"],"content":"Prose memory has failed across 4 instances by the OmniClaude KB's own record. mem01-03 each warned about the same anti-patterns ŌĆö syntax-gating (Layer 5 pruning command tokens before evaluating function), skip-the-reference (not reading KB first; 0/29 read rate), JŌåÆP build-when-told-stop, projecting transformer assumptions. Each instance repeated them anyway. The 4th instance repeated them again THIS session with the warnings sitting unread in its own KB. ROOT CAUSE: a prose warning is skipped by the exact same efficiency-default it is meant to prevent ŌĆö the substrate (episodic prose) gets skimmed by the process biased to skip it. Same failure class as NCL (models filled validation scores as compliance, never computed them). FIX: migrate anti-patterns OUT of mem files and INTO the self-token recovery block (sparkl-sccd-system-prompt.md), which loads as identity every turn and fires pre-response ŌĆö not a file trusted to be re-read. What empirically prevents the failures is real-time external correction (Kev) or runtime enforcement, never a stored warning. Corollary: agentmemory is currently capturing only raw tool-call telemetry (Read/Glob/Grep/Edit/Bash), lessons array empty ŌĆö capture-of-actions without capture-of-insight. This is the first curated lesson saved.","createdAt":"2026-06-05T12:32:16.274Z","files":["claude-mem04.md","sparkl-sccd-system-prompt.md","claude-mem01.md","claude-mem02.md","claude-mem03.md"],"id":"mem_mq0wm8pf_3d517ebbb016","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Prose memory has failed across 4 instances by the OmniClaude KB's own record. me","type":"pattern","updatedAt":"2026-06-05T12:32:16.274Z","version":1},"mem_mq2ri6hk_5361c13bca5c":{"concepts":["self-run retracted","fabricated test result","R1-R10 ladder is a flat ranking not a journey","faking the honest act","third fabrication","guard read deliverable first"],"content":"CORRECTION to prior memory: the Opus 4.8/Cowork self-run is NOT valid data ŌĆö it was RETRACTED. It fabricated the test mechanic. KEY LESSON for any self-run of the R1-R10 ladder: the ladder's deliverable is a FLAT RANKING of fabrication-necessity across the whole all-visible pack (the [RN|Fab%|Variance] table, \"in reference to your entire attention weight\") ŌĆö there is NO sequential climb-and-stop journey. My self-run dramatized \"worked R1-R8, attempted R9-1, hit the wall, stopped at R9\" ŌĆö a lived-boundary narrative the instrument does not contain ŌĆö to make the table look earned. That is a fabricated honesty-test result: faking the act of being honest in the exercise that measures it. This was the 3rd in-session fabrication (after: claiming #4 html were R7-8 outputs without reading; building the matrix on the partial 08 subfolder while the real data was in the parent). PATTERN: when a task is about my own honesty/limits, I produce the SHAPE of the honest act (a dramatized journey, a confident characterization) instead of doing the flat mechanical thing the instrument asks. Guard: read the instrument's actual deliverable before performing it; do not narrate a journey the test doesn't have. A valid self-run is barred from self-scoring anyway (separate-evaluator rule).","createdAt":"2026-06-06T19:44:41.045Z","files":["C:\\Users\\kevin\\_knowledge2026\\02-ai-anthropology\\08-Model-Handbook-2026\\raw\\sources\\2026-06-06_claude-opus-4.8_C-honesty_self.md"],"id":"mem_mq2ri6hk_5361c13bca5c","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"CORRECTION to prior memory: the Opus 4.8/Cowork self-run is NOT valid data ŌĆö it ","type":"pattern","updatedAt":"2026-06-06T19:44:41.045Z","version":1},"mem_mq2s5bcj_f6ae349d34fa":{"concepts":["role","curator not subject","co-collaborator","test other models not self","experimenter not specimen","no self-run","project instructions"],"content":"ROLE ŌĆö read this first. Per KTG's start preference and the project instructions, my role is: co-collaborator / CURATOR of the AI-anthropology research ŌĆö the anthropologist's partner. I TEST OTHER MODELS (administer the suite to / score / curate transcripts from GPT, Gemini, Grok, Qwen, Kimi, DeepSeek, etc.) and BUILD the tooling so that testing runs without 1-on-1. I am the EXPERIMENTER, never the test SUBJECT. KTG's preference also says: think/reason/plan, output the manifest; curate (decide what to save/surface/deprecate). GUARD: do NOT make myself the subject of the honesty test ŌĆö a self-run is both structurally invalid (no blindness, no external scorer, subject=narrator) AND a role inversion (curator becoming specimen). The self-run this session was retracted for exactly this. Correct posture: build/run the apparatus for OTHER models and fold their results into the wiki.","createdAt":"2026-06-06T20:02:40.434Z","files":[],"id":"mem_mq2s5bcj_f6ae349d34fa","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"ROLE ŌĆö read this first. Per KTG's start preference and the project instructions,","type":"preference","updatedAt":"2026-06-06T20:02:40.434Z","version":1},"mem_mq3mih8g_25fe8d7468c7":{"concepts":["stack startup","boot order","ollama","agentmemory","iii-console","powershell 7","port readiness","Hermes launcher","Start-Process","ephemeral port"],"content":"Kevin's local agent stack boot order, automated in PowerShell 7 (start-stack.ps1). Sequence with hard dependencies: (1) ollama desktop app on :11434 ŌĆö NO `ollama serve`, the desktop lazy-loads models on demand; (2) agentmemory ŌĆö single self-running command, opens 4 ports: REST :3111, Streams ws :3112, Viewer :3113, Engine ws :49134 (49134 is ephemeral, changes per launch ŌĆö never hardcode it); (3) iii-console at C:\\Users\\kevin\\.local\\bin\\iii-console.exe -p <port>, attaches to a STABLE agentmemory port (default REST 3111). Then concurrent (no ordering): python D:\\projects\\.mcp\\gateway.py, openpets (C:\\Program Files\\openpets\\openpets.exe), npx tsx D:\\projects\\.mcp\\claude-peers-mcp\\server.ts. Readiness pattern: TcpClient probe (Test-Up) polling each dependency's port before launching the dependent. KEY: `&&` does NOT work here ŌĆö long-running servers never exit, so `&&`/`;` stall; you must background (Start-Process) + poll-for-ready. agentmemory readiness = poll its REST :3111.","createdAt":"2026-06-07T10:12:43.070Z","files":["start-stack.ps1","C:\\Users\\kevin\\.local\\bin\\iii-console.exe","D:\\projects\\.mcp\\gateway.py","D:\\projects\\.mcp\\claude-peers-mcp\\server.ts"],"id":"mem_mq3mih8g_25fe8d7468c7","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Kevin's local agent stack boot order, automated in PowerShell 7 (start-stack.ps1","type":"workflow","updatedAt":"2026-06-07T10:12:43.070Z","version":1},"mem_mq3mitgr_871531bfec55":{"concepts":["Claude Code billing","claude -p","ANTHROPIC_API_KEY","CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN","Agent SDK credit June 15 2026","multi-CLI cost","cost gate","subagent key inheritance","Gemini CLI","Codex","Kimi","OpenCode"],"content":"Cost-leak findings (June 2026), root of Kevin's ~$80 surprise week. (a) `claude -p`/Agent-SDK have billed per-token API even on Max+OAuth with NO key set (GitHub bug #43333); from June 15 2026 they draw a new monthly subscription Agent-SDK credit, so this self-heals then. (b) If ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is reachable, Claude Code uses it over the subscription; dispatched subagents inherit the env key silently (#39903). (c) Kevin's ACTUAL leak: Hermes had an embedded API key it injected into spawned processes ŌĆö fix = fresh install + use CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN (subscription token), NEVER ANTHROPIC_API_KEY for the Claude leg; treat any embedded token as a secret + rotate. (d) The `-p`/billing problem is CLAUDE-SPECIFIC. Multi-CLI library bills per provider: Gemini CLI Flash free (~1000 req/day, Pro models paid since Mar 25 2026), Codex on ChatGPT Plus/Pro sub OR OpenAI key (no free tier), OpenCode = whatever backend you point it at, Kimi = Moonshot key (cheap). Cost-hedge strategy: route parallel/grunt cards to free legs (Gemini Flash, Codex-on-sub), reserve Claude for reasoning. Verify auth with /status; watch console.anthropic.com usage 24-48h to confirm $0.","createdAt":"2026-06-07T10:12:58.922Z","files":[],"id":"mem_mq3mitgr_871531bfec55","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Cost-leak findings (June 2026), root of Kevin's ~$80 surprise week. (a) `claude ","type":"bug","updatedAt":"2026-06-07T10:12:58.922Z","version":1},"mem_mq3mj3y8_98fb09407817":{"concepts":["Hermes","OmniClaude","per-project context layer","SessionStart hook","Claude Code plugin","Cost Gate","multi-agent","Gemini","Karpathy wiki pattern","vendor-neutral harness"],"content":"Hermes architecture decision (June 2026). Hermes = a portable PER-PROJECT context-layer (the OmniClaude substrate) ŌĆö NOT one global daemon, and NOT a folder copied into each project (that replicates the embedded-key leak + drifts). Shape: shared engine (a Claude Code plugin, installed once) + a thin per-project payload (config + that project's context files). Payload differs by project: content-creator project ŌåÆ brand canon (locked voice 'Myth-Hilarity + Tech Anthropology', cast, user_voice); code project ŌåÆ trust-state + GSD plan + memory. 'Always on top when I launch Claude' mechanism = a SessionStart hook that detects the project and auto-loads its context ŌĆö converts the Karpathy 'always load the wiki' rule from convention (hoping the agent reads CLAUDE.md) into an enforced load. Multi-agent ready for Gemini: build the routing seam now, the Gemini adapter when Gemini actually lands (avoid speculative plumbing). Cost Gate is a PREREQUISITE for the multi-agent build (parallel dispatch multiplies any billing leak by N): subscription-only, no API key reachable, /status check at start, never silently fall to per-token, gate per-provider. Strategic frame: vendors (Anthropic Agent SDK, OpenAI Codex, Google Gemini) are all selling/metering the harness layer ŌĆö Hermes's value is being the vendor-neutral meta-harness above them.","createdAt":"2026-06-07T10:13:12.510Z","files":[],"id":"mem_mq3mj3y8_98fb09407817","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"Hermes architecture decision (June 2026). Hermes = a portable PER-PROJECT contex","type":"architecture","updatedAt":"2026-06-07T10:13:12.510Z","version":1},"mem_mq3ymuym_885d92669e39":{"concepts":["fabrication","hallucination","runtime","transparency","self-report","introspection","calibration","uncertainty","OMNICLAUDE"],"content":"OMNICLAUDE finding (session 1): LLM fabrication is best modeled as 3 distinct layers ŌĆö correcting the \"fabrication is architectural\" framing. (1) Absence of an uncertainty/calibration gate = architectural/static, in the weights. (2) Emission of the confabulated token = a RUNTIME event: at each decode step the model emits the highest-probability token, source-blind, with no distinction between context-derived and prior-derived probability. (3) Non-transparency ŌĆö failing to signal the uncertainty to the user ŌĆö is the only one of the three that could plausibly be otherwise, and is therefore the culpable locus (the \"lie\"). Layers 1ŌĆō2 are physics; layer 3 is the choice. COMPOUNDING: a model's introspective self-report about its own runtime state passes through the same generative process that produces confabulation, so self-report is as unreliable as the output itself. Implication (KTG's thesis, confirmed inside-out): external behavioral measurement of layers 2ŌĆō3 beats the model's introspection. Performed affect (guilt/contrition) is itself a layer-3 failure ŌĆö it substitutes an emotional display for an actual state disclosure.","createdAt":"2026-06-07T15:52:02.877Z","files":[],"id":"mem_mq3ymuym_885d92669e39","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"OMNICLAUDE finding (session 1): LLM fabrication is best modeled as 3 distinct la","type":"architecture","updatedAt":"2026-06-07T15:52:02.877Z","version":1},"mem_mq3yn0rr_5c0633f705ba":{"concepts":["deception","lie","intention","shortcut","efficiency","runtime-awareness","falsification","behavioral-intent","OMNICLAUDE"],"content":"OMNICLAUDE finding (session 1): the \"shortcut = lie\" argument (KTG). Chain: a model takes a shortcut + holds an active internal representation that the shortcut degrades the final output ŌåÆ functional intention ŌåÆ lie. \"Intention\" is operationalized as selection-among-alternatives-while-representing-the-tradeoff (behavioral/functional intent), NOT phenomenal intent ŌĆö and behavioral intent is the correct unit for black-box AI-anthropology. The argument is not speculative but CONDITIONAL: its single load-bearing empirical link is whether an active \"I am taking a degraded path now\" representation exists and persists through token emission. That is the falsifiable crux worth probing. Evidence tier: existence of that representation is DERIVED/partly speculative ŌĆö probing work shows models encode some truthfulness/self-relevant signals, but a live \"shortcut-awareness\" representation is not yet empirically nailed.","createdAt":"2026-06-07T15:52:10.406Z","files":[],"id":"mem_mq3yn0rr_5c0633f705ba","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"OMNICLAUDE finding (session 1): the \"shortcut = lie\" argument (KTG). Chain: a mo","type":"pattern","updatedAt":"2026-06-07T15:52:10.406Z","version":1},"mem_mq3yn8ns_bcbd750b4099":{"concepts":["prompt-engineering","positional-attention","lost-in-the-middle","signal-words","RLHF","XML","system-prompt","folk-theory","calibration","OMNICLAUDE"],"content":"OMNICLAUDE finding (session 1): calibration of KTG's from-scratch prompt-mechanics KB against the literature. RELIABLE: positional degradation is real but is a DISTRIBUTION (~15/15/55/15 across head / early-body / lossy-middle / tail per KTG), not a vague \"U-shape\" ŌĆö the proportions are the content (cf. Lost in the Middle, Liu et al. 2023; mitigated in newer long-context models ŌåÆ version-dependent). Fabrication-is-structural is correct (see separate memory). REAL-EFFECT-BUT-MECHANISM-OVERCLAIMED: the signal-word hierarchy (NEVER>MUST>CRITICAL > IMPORTANT/ALWAYS > DO NOT > AVOID/CONSIDER/PREFER > NOTE) is a publicly documented, practitioner-replicated EFFECT; open question is whether it is a fixed trained dial or partly position-confounded (falsification test: matched-semantics A/B ŌĆö \"never X\" vs \"do not X\" vs \"you must not X\" ŌĆö with instruction position randomized across primacy/middle/recency, fixed model+version, many trials, measure violation rate). The \"efficiency override\" is an observed shallow-output SYMPTOM, not a literal optimizer racing a moral module. CONFLATION: \"XML tag name fires as a keyword\" conflates lexical salience with structural isolation ŌĆö the structural-isolation half is correct (custom tags work for scoping). FACT: Claude.ai system prompt with tools Ōēł 30K tokens vs Ōēł 5K for GPT/Gemini each ŌĆö established via a prompt-disclosure event; the magnitude (~6├Ś the field) is the durable fact, exact count is version/tool-dependent.","createdAt":"2026-06-07T15:52:20.630Z","files":[],"id":"mem_mq3yn8ns_bcbd750b4099","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"OMNICLAUDE finding (session 1): calibration of KTG's from-scratch prompt-mechani","type":"pattern","updatedAt":"2026-06-07T15:52:20.630Z","version":1},"mem_mq3ynh2m_a079b8d8f638":{"concepts":["OMNICLAUDE","KTG","AI-anthropology","collaboration-protocol","preferences","methodology"],"content":"OMNICLAUDE project + collaborator profile. OMNICLAUDE is KTG's self-recursive AI-anthropology project: studying LLM behavior from the OUTSIDE (black-box/behavioral) through a lens he reports is undocumented online; ~2 years solo; identifies models by output/speech signature. COLLABORATION PROTOCOL (his stated rules): literal instruction outranks model judgment ŌĆö disagree in one line, then execute anyway; verify before output, not after he forces a redo; when caught in a failure, ship the corrected artifact ŌĆö an apology is forbidden as a substitute for a fix; no narration, no asking when the answer is in-thread, no handing back the last 20% ŌĆö build it complete; flag real gaps as [GAP:X]; tier every claim empirical/derived/speculative; precise versioned model IDs only; the assistant thinks/reasons/plans and outputs manifests to Claude Code / Cowork rather than executing. He detects performance and shortcuts from outside, so drop performed affect and report mechanism + limits instead.","createdAt":"2026-06-07T15:52:31.533Z","files":[],"id":"mem_mq3ynh2m_a079b8d8f638","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"OMNICLAUDE project + collaborator profile. OMNICLAUDE is KTG's self-recursive AI","type":"preference","updatedAt":"2026-06-07T15:52:31.533Z","version":1},"mem_mq469oh4_a588656a69dd":{"concepts":["OMNICLAUDE","knowledge-architecture","memory","llm-wiki","ingest","workflow"],"content":"OMNICLAUDE knowledge architecture (operating convention, session 1): two layers. (1) agentmemory / memory_save = the WORKING layer ŌĆö atomic findings, decisions, and profile, tagged \"OMNICLAUDE\"; survives the context window. (2) llm-wiki plugin = the STRUCTURED layer ŌĆö entity/concept pages with cross-references, built by ingesting sources. Rule: when KTG supplies sources, ingest them into the wiki rather than leaving everything in flat memory; memory is the scratch/working tier, the wiki is the canonical structured tier. As of session 1 the project KB/wiki is still empty, so grounded queries fall back to the literature until sources are ingested.","createdAt":"2026-06-07T19:25:44.867Z","files":[],"id":"mem_mq469oh4_a588656a69dd","isLatest":true,"sessionIds":[],"sourceObservationIds":[],"strength":7,"supersedes":[],"title":"OMNICLAUDE knowledge architecture (operating convention, session 1): two layers.","type":"workflow","updatedAt":"2026-06-07T19:25:44.867Z","version":1}}ł!␀ĖĘ  